♪ What you wanna do? ♪

17:47.330 --> 17:49.540
♪ Go, go, go, go ♪

17:49.540 --> 17:51.460
♪ Go, go ♪

17:51.460 --> 17:52.380
♪ What you wanna do? ♪

17:52.380 --> 17:54.830
♪ Go, go, go, go ♪

17:54.830 --> 17:57.540
♪ Go, go, go, go ♪

17:57.540 --> 17:58.620
♪ Go ♪

18:01.420 --> 18:02.790
Does this thing
actually talk?

18:02.790 --> 18:04.920
If so, it better
say thank you.

18:04.920 --> 18:06.670
Hmm, all those mouthfuls

18:06.670 --> 18:08.750
of dust bunnies and cobwebs
are gonna be worth it.

18:08.750 --> 18:10.540
We're gonna make
Dad's dream come true.

18:11.540 --> 18:13.620
[engine starts]

18:13.620 --> 18:14.670
[brakes screech]

18:14.670 --> 18:17.460
[mournful musical flourish]

18:17.460 --> 18:18.830
Do you think
Dad has a dream

18:18.830 --> 18:20.580
to tow
the Crimson Coupe?

18:20.580 --> 18:23.000
-[car sizzles]
-[Harley coughs]

18:25.670 --> 18:27.880
Be sure to tell your friends
we're closed.

18:27.880 --> 18:29.790
[sighs]

18:31.620 --> 18:33.710
[sighs]
All right, instead of

18:33.710 --> 18:36.540
a festive bib, yummy sides,
and fancy china,

18:36.540 --> 18:38.710
we've got a tarp, chips,
and chipped plates.

18:38.710 --> 18:40.830
But the headliner's lobster.

18:40.830 --> 18:43.250
No one cares about
the opening acts anyway.

18:45.080 --> 18:46.500
[Ethan]
They're gone!

18:46.500 --> 18:47.580
Someone must've
stolen them.

18:47.580 --> 18:48.540
Well, they sure didn't

18:48.540 --> 18:49.750
walk out of here
on their own.

18:49.750 --> 18:50.830
Right. I mean, yeah,

18:50.830 --> 18:52.080
the coolers
are flipped over

18:52.080 --> 18:53.750
and there's trails
of water leading

18:53.750 --> 18:56.500
-all over the store, but...
-[gasps] They escaped!

18:56.500 --> 18:58.380
There's animals
with giant pinchers

18:58.380 --> 18:59.460
loose all over the store!

18:59.460 --> 19:01.580
Mom, Mom, relax.
They can't hurt us.

19:01.580 --> 19:03.170
They have rubber bands
around their claws.

19:03.170 --> 19:04.250
Like those?

19:07.620 --> 19:09.170
-Run! Aah!
-[Suzy screaming]

19:09.170 --> 19:12.170
[both screaming]

19:14.620 --> 19:16.500
What a disaster.

19:16.500 --> 19:18.580
Instead of taking on
Dad's nightmare,

19:18.580 --> 19:19.960
we created a new one.

19:19.960 --> 19:21.620
We didn't
clean the garage,

19:21.620 --> 19:22.960
and now we're gonna
ruin his day off

19:22.960 --> 19:24.460
by making him
come get us.

19:24.460 --> 19:27.330
Hmm. He spent all day
with Daphne.

19:27.330 --> 19:29.290
Maybe he'll welcome
the break.

19:29.290 --> 19:30.620
[tires squealing, explosion]

19:30.620 --> 19:32.040
Ooh! Explosion!

19:32.040 --> 19:33.670
Brownie me.

19:33.670 --> 19:34.920
[Mike Justice]
I'm beginning to think

19:34.920 --> 19:36.670
this ghost town isn't empty.

19:36.670 --> 19:38.670
[Coupe]
Spooky.

19:38.670 --> 19:40.540
Mm, cheesy guitar riff.

19:40.540 --> 19:41.540
What do we eat now?
Jelly beans?

19:41.540 --> 19:43.620
No, churro.
Jelly beans are for

19:43.620 --> 19:45.380
when Mike takes off
his sunglasses.

19:45.380 --> 19:48.540
[Mike Justice]
...and let's do this.

19:48.540 --> 19:51.250
-Oh, there they go.
-These shady cattle ranchers

19:51.250 --> 19:53.080
have roped their last
prized steer, Coupe.

19:53.080 --> 19:54.500
[Coupe]
Giddy up, bro.

19:56.040 --> 19:57.080
[Mike Justice]
Hold on, Coupe.

19:57.080 --> 19:58.620
Let me stretch first.

19:58.620 --> 20:00.250
Ahh, stretching's important.

20:00.250 --> 20:02.580
Oh, teaching a lesson.
Gotta have the broccoli.

20:02.580 --> 20:04.580
Ugh, you had to throw in
one healthy food.

20:04.580 --> 20:06.330
[phone ringing]

20:06.330 --> 20:08.040
[Coupe]
Junk in my trunk.

20:08.040 --> 20:10.500
Ha, ha, ha, ha.

20:10.500 --> 20:11.750
Harley?

20:11.750 --> 20:12.750
Don't tell her
what we're doing.

20:12.750 --> 20:13.750
She'll want in.

20:13.750 --> 20:15.040
This is our game, bro.

20:15.040 --> 20:16.540
Ooh! Drink!

20:17.670 --> 20:20.250
Mm? What?

20:21.710 --> 20:22.920
First things first.
Are you girls okay?

20:22.920 --> 20:23.920
-Yeah.
-Yes.

20:23.920 --> 20:25.080
Good.

20:25.080 --> 20:26.420
It's the Crimson Coupe,

20:26.420 --> 20:27.540
the Crimson Coupe!

20:27.540 --> 20:29.710
How did you get
the Crimson Coupe?

20:29.710 --> 20:32.960
It was supposed to be
your birthday present.

20:32.960 --> 20:34.170
I'm sorry.

20:35.500 --> 20:36.670
For what?

20:36.670 --> 20:38.540
For making you
miss that message.

20:38.540 --> 20:40.670
The Diazes are
notoriously late.

20:40.670 --> 20:43.080
Who did I think I was
being six days early?

20:43.080 --> 20:44.670
You were just being born.

20:44.670 --> 20:46.380
You didn't know
family traditions.

20:46.380 --> 20:49.540
Yeah, but because of me
you had to sacrifice the car.

20:49.540 --> 20:52.580
And now you had to
sacrifice your day off
to come and get us.

20:52.580 --> 20:54.040
You know what
that's called?

20:54.040 --> 20:55.500
Being a parent.

20:55.500 --> 20:57.080
I knew that when I
signed up for it,

20:57.080 --> 20:58.710
and I love it.

20:58.710 --> 20:59.670
[sighs]

20:59.670 --> 21:02.080
Nothing I do
for you guys

21:02.080 --> 21:04.960
as a dad is ever
a sacrifice.

21:04.960 --> 21:07.920
In fact, I got
a great idea.

21:13.210 --> 21:14.790
By the time we're done
restoring this,

21:14.790 --> 21:16.210
it'll be just like
it was on the show.

21:16.210 --> 21:17.750
Yeah, so it's not
gonna talk.

21:17.750 --> 21:18.710
That was TV magic.

21:18.710 --> 21:21.420
It could with
a little Harley magic.

21:21.420 --> 21:23.790
You see? This car
is gonna be way better

21:23.790 --> 21:25.670
than if I'd won it
15 years ago.

21:25.670 --> 21:28.580
Make sure Coupey
knows how to say,
"Crime is wack!"

21:28.580 --> 21:31.080
I thought it was dumb,
but it's kinda grown on me.

21:31.080 --> 21:33.080
-[all chuckle]
-[Daphne] Here.

21:33.080 --> 21:34.710
[laughs]

21:34.710 --> 21:36.000
I love being a dad.

21:36.000 --> 21:38.580
[Suzy]
Was that in the garage?

21:38.580 --> 21:41.500
Man, we really did need
to clean that thing out.

21:41.500 --> 21:42.580
The girls got it for me.

21:45.380 --> 21:47.120
Uh, oh. Sorry.

21:47.120 --> 21:49.210
All we got you
was BunBurger...

21:49.210 --> 21:50.750
like we do every year.

21:50.750 --> 21:52.710
Yeah, and every year
it's my favortie.

21:52.710 --> 21:55.170
Favorite burger,
favorite car,

21:55.170 --> 21:56.250
favorite family.

21:57.670 --> 21:59.620
I have never felt
so re-appreciated.

22:00.620 --> 22:03.290
Bring it in!

22:03.290 --> 22:04.750
So, are we gonna tell him

22:04.750 --> 22:06.250
we didn't clean out
the garage?

22:06.250 --> 22:07.670
If I get this thing
talking fast enough,

22:07.670 --> 22:08.790
we'll have the car
break it to him.

22:08.790 --> 22:09.620
Mm.

22:09.620 --> 22:11.670
[all chattering]

22:11.670 --> 22:12.750
[Suzy]
Should we eat?

22:12.750 --> 22:14.290
Let's do it!

22:14.290 --> 22:16.290
Best birthday ever!

22:16.290 --> 22:17.580
Birthday dinner.

22:17.580 --> 22:19.580
[all chattering]
